---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Lockfud Privacy Policy">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-800">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-4">
      Lockfud Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="italic text-gray-500 mb-6">Last Updated: June 2026</p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      Lockfud is a food diary app that lets you photograph your meals,
      automatically cut out the food into stickers, and log them to a
      calendar-based journal. This policy explains how your data is handled.
      In short: everything stays on your device.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      Personal Information
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Lockfud does not collect, store, or share any personal user data. The app
      has no accounts, no sign-in, and no backend server. You do not provide any
      personal information to use it.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      What stays on your device
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      All of your content is stored locally on your device and is never uploaded
      to us or anyone else. This includes:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2">
      <li>The meal photos you capture or import</li>
      <li>The food stickers generated from those photos</li>
      <li>Optional text captions you add to a meal</li>
      <li>Meal dates and timestamps used to build your diary and statistics</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-4">
      We have no access to this data. It remains on your device until you delete
      a meal or remove the app.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      On-Device Food Detection
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      To turn your photo into a sticker, Lockfud uses Apple's Vision framework
      (on iOS 17 and later) to isolate the food subject from the background. This
      processing happens entirely on your device — your photos are never sent to
      a server for analysis. If no subject can be detected, the original photo is
      used instead.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Permissions</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Camera</strong> — used to take photos of your meals from within
        the app. Photos are saved only to your device.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Photo Library</strong> — used only when you choose to import an
        existing photo to log as a meal.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Permissions are requested only when needed, and the app does not access
      your camera or photos in the background.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      Third-Party Services
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Lockfud does not use any third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking
      services. It does not make network requests with your meal data and works
      offline.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      Children's Privacy
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Lockfud is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly
      collect any data from them. Because no data is collected at all, the app is
      safe for users of all ages.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Your choices</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Because your data is stored locally, you are in full control. You can
      delete individual meals at any time, and deleting the app removes all of
      your stored meals and photos. There is no account to close.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      Changes to This Policy
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      We may update this privacy policy from time to time. The "Last Updated"
      date above will reflect the latest version.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Contact</h2>
    <p class="mb-2">
      If you have any questions about this policy, email
      <a
        href="mailto:getvisiblelondon@gmail.com"
        class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">getvisiblelondon@gmail.com</a
      >.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-500">— Lockfud</p>
  </div>
</Layout>
